<subSubSection id="25AD655A13155C4BFF15FDDDCF9DFD0C" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" type="description">
<paragraph id="6D0836D113155C4BFF15FDDDC97FFDCF" blockId="17.[174,1232,575,698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Widespread in the Palaearctic and Nearctic Regions (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013155C4BFBE8FDA2CDFEFDCF" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." pageId="17" pageNumber="470" refId="ref19613" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Volume 1. Agromyzinae. Nagykovacsi, Pars Ltd., 1 - 416. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.18655 / Agromyzidae. Vol. 1." type="book" year="2015">Papp &amp; Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313155C4BFF08FDC2CC9EFDCC" bold="true" box="[254,395,607,633]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
In 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113155C4BFED6FDC2CC93FDCC" box="[288,390,607,633]" name="Ukraine" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313155C4BFE64FDC2CF5EFDCC" box="[402,587,607,633]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Kharkiv Region</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013155C4BFDACFDC2CFEFFDCF" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[602,762,607,634]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref19116" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2012. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 2. 14 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The first record of Melanagromyza provecta (de Meijere, 1910) for Europe. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (2), 56 - 62 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Guglya, 2012</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313155C4BFCFBFDC2CEAAFDCC" box="[781,959,607,633]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313155C4BFC26FDC2C94CFDCC" bold="true" box="[976,1113,607,633]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">first record</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D113155C4BFF15FDE2CF9DFD0C" blockId="17.[174,1232,575,698]" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">
Bionomics. Common in 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313155C4BFDD1FDE2CFC9FD2C" box="[551,732,639,665]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
, but not so in the rest of 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113155C4BFBE4FDE2C960FD2C" box="[1042,1141,639,665]" name="Ukraine" pageId="17" pageNumber="470">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
. Adults were caught from 29 April to 24 August.
</paragraph>
